Here's how to run the app now:

  Installation (First Time)

  # From the project directory
  ./install.sh

  This installs the json-holygrail command globally in your environment.

  Running the App

  Basic Usage

  # Convert a JSON file to markdown (uses default format)
  json-holygrail examples/trade-plan-FCEL-2025-12-18.json

  # This creates: examples/trade-plan-FCEL-2025-12-18.md

  With Different Formats

  # Use compact format
  json-holygrail examples/trade-plan-FCEL-2025-12-18.json --format compact

  # Use custom template
  json-holygrail examples/trade-plan-FCEL-2025-12-18.json --format /path/to/custom.md

  # Specify output file
  json-holygrail input.json -o output.md

  Other Commands

  # List available formats
  json-holygrail --list-formats

  # Show version
  json-holygrail --version

  # Show help
  json-holygrail --help

  Alternative: Direct Python Execution

  If you haven't installed it yet, you can also run it directly:

  # Using uv (development)
  uv run json-holygrail input.json

  # Or as a module
  uv run python -m json_holygrail.main input.json

  Quick Test

  Try it right now with the example file:

  json-holygrail examples/trade-plan-FCEL-2025-12-18.json --format compact

  This will create examples/trade-plan-FCEL-2025-12-18.md with the compact format!
